We had a great time here!  I ordered the Rosewater Lemonade (tasted like regular lemonade to me, nothin special) and my friend got the Turkish coffee which took awhile, as it normally does, and tasted great.  We are both vegan and the waitress seemed to have a good sense of what was vegan on the menu. She was unsure of the hummus but asked the kitchen to be certain.  I ordered a mixture of sides that were all lovely. The hummus stuck out to me as being fantastic, along with the grape leaves. I don’t remember the names of what else I got but they were tasty!  My friend ordered the vegetable sandwich which she liked very much.  We ate in the garden which I highly recommend. It’s cute and has good vibes.  The only negative is that once we were done eating, it took the waitress a very long time to get our check. Not sure if this is a cultural thing, being that in the Middle East and Europe people tend to stay and talk after eating, but we were anxious to leave and stayed 20 minutes longer than we wanted to. We ended up asking one of the cooks to grab our server and she got everything settled.

Dear Chef: I've been a huge fan of Zaytoons for many, many years.  Your lentil soup and chicken pizza has been a great stable take-out dinner that I frequently pick up on my way home from work. So, on a  particular rainy night last week, I couldn't WAIT to get home and chow down.  WHAT HAPPENED? Did you have a bad day? or did you change the recipe for the chicken pizza?  It was so bad I spit it out. The bread was burnt, the chicken was tough and flavored with negligence. Then, because I was so hungry and have loyal faith in the quality Zaytoons food, I heated it up and tried again. I should say, heated up the only three pieces that had any food on it, the other half was naked bread, and not because the food had slipped off in transport; nothing had been there in the first place. Heat only made dry chicken drier and the poor choice of herbal rub even more potent. If you had one bad day, all is forgiven. But if you've lost all love for your community of chicken pizza fans, please just take it off the menu and don't torture us again.

Delicious food, very authentic. And I'm a foodie. Ordered from here 3 days consecutively for a large group of people and got to sample many items. And one in the group was Israeli, also a foodie. And he gave it very high praise  -- and he's very critical!  Babaganoush was tastier than hummus, though they were both yummy. Comes with freshly made, thin pita/flatbread that's amazing. Personally liked the chicken shawarma more than the chicken kabob. More flavor. But both were equally as fresh. Also had tabouleh, grape leaves, salad, rice, and it was all amazing.  All the food is very fresh and high quality!  Friendly helpful staff, though the first time I called I was put on hold (phone was placed on counter) then I was forgotten about and couldn't call back because it gave me a busy signal. :P So I had to order via Grubhub online instead. Also had a complaint about silverware and napkins that were left out of the delivery a couple of times.
great service, nice ambiance, and yummy grub at affordable prices.  great with kids too.
We love Zaytoons!  Restaurant is great and outdoor garden area is beautiful.  Our favorites so far have been the pizza (veggies are amazing) and the couscous.
Excellent Mediterranean food. Doesn't look like much and it's cash only last time I checked, but it's good.
The food is so delicious and good value. The lamb leg platter is the best
Food is incredible, prices are affordable, but the service is show especially for a Friday night.

Chill atmosphere, great service, affordable prices. I was visiting the city and a friend recommended this place. Very glad they did. I had the Mediterranean burger (messy, but worth it; ask for extra napkins), fries and a Stella.
AMAZING food! 3 people ate our fill for $25! I don't even know how they stay open with such incredible prices and lovely decor!
I really enjoyed the flatbreads. Excellent prices for the area.
Authentic Middle  Eastern food. Not much in terms of variety though.
One of my favorite Arab restaurants. Great quality tasty food! And the price is extremely reasonable! Must visit!
Been  going here for years. Delicious food with generous portions
Combo plate was delicious.
Reasonably priced food, and an awesome patio out back.
Whenever I'm back in Brooklyn, this is on my Must Go list. Great food. My favorite option is the platter of 5 starters.

Great customer service...very casual, laid back, family style feel. Food is not only cheap, but very good as well. BYOB friendly too. The goat cheese pizza and the burger with the apples in it are really good.
Spinach pie was delicious. Outdoor seating was also nice

If I could rate just the delicioussss food, I'd give 5 stars for sure! Prices (food & wine) also deserve a 5, really reasonably priced for great quality. But the service is more of a 3.5/4. But regardless, highly recommend!! It's one of my favorite places. In the warmer weather, the garden in the back is beautiful!
Go here now whenever I'm in the area, their baked chicken is so good and price is reasonable for all the food served. Their service is good as well, never feel rushed and always polite.
So good! Our entire party of 14 loved their food, evidenced by quiet overtaking the restaurant as soon as we were served. Great value too, portions are huge.
Mediocre food.

Maybe we just went on a bad night, but the food we experienced at Zaytoons left a lot to be desired. It was mostly unmemorable, tasteless, and dry. I had the chicken in rice which I thought would be pretty hard to mess up but dry chicken will really ruin a dish every time. They do have a big menu, and are reasonably priced. Service was good. The house wine was putrid.
I waited an hour for delivery. I called to check in on things. The delivery guy had already given my food to the wrong address. Hungry and disappointed.

Very good standard middle eastern fare in pleasant surroundings. Falafel was fresh and hot. Chicken shawarma was very good. Price was reasonable. Cash only, which is super annoying and for which I docked one star. Otherwise four star on food.
you are very good
The food is excellent and the garden (when available) is a lovely place to sit.
Consistently excellent food. Good service and prices. Cozy atmosphere for dining and reliable delivery. My current favorite in the area.

I love this place because the food is so reasonably-priced and authentic. The laid-back vibe makes this place great to come with a group of friends or on a date. The chicken shawarma platter is absolutely delicious as is the hummus and babaghanouj, which is super fresh. I'm pretty sure I saw people smoking hookah in the back here as well. I wish that this place was BYOB like their other locations though, as well as accepting credit cards.
Well executed basics. They also have some burgers and other american dishes you can safely skip.

Stick to the basics and you'll have a fine meal. Ironically, for a place that touts Middle Eastern style pizza the Lahmahjihn is awful. The standards, babaganoush, houmous, etc are great and the flat bread they serve it with is perfection!
I love the leafy backyard here in the summer. The food is solid but not amazing. Great for the price though!

Don't get delivery. This food is made to be eaten straight from the kitchen and gets soggy and muddled in flavor if you order it out. Lots of lemon, fresh veggies, its a good way to break up the usual places people eat at

One of a few locations. Great fresh salads and other standard Middle Eastern fare. BYOB and this location has a back garden that is great in the warmer months. fresh pita made in house and ask for the hot sauce it's tasty and spicy without being overly hot. fast service and you are never rushed out.
Very solid pick for mid east food.  I get the chicken shawarma platter, really good and cheap price.
I've gotten delivery from here many times, the food is delicious!
